---
// PrimaryMission.astro — AesCode Co. v2.0
// Simple restrained single-column editorial section
---

<section class="mission section-primary" id="mission" aria-labelledby="mission-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="mission__inner">

      <div class="mission__label-col reveal">
        <p class="label-sm" style="color: var(--accent);">THE PLATFORM</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mission__content">
        <h2 id="mission-heading" class="display-md serif italic text-primary mb-xl reveal reveal--delay-1">
          Three layers. One flywheel.
        </h2>
        <div class="hairline hairline--short hairline--accent mb-2xl reveal reveal--delay-1"></div>

        <div class="mission__layers">

          <div class="mission__layer reveal reveal--delay-1">
            <div class="mission__layer-header">
              <span class="mono data-md text-accent mission__layer-num">LAYER 0</span>
              <h3 class="mission__layer-title serif text-primary">Talent Engine</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="body-md" style="color: var(--on-surface-variant);">
              Recurring cohorts surface engineering teams working on real clinical problems from Bharati Hospital. The best teams advance to the next layer.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mission__connector" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="mono data-sm" style="color: var(--outline);">↓</span>
          </div>

          <div class="mission__layer reveal reveal--delay-2">
            <div class="mission__layer-header">
              <span class="mono data-md text-accent mission__layer-num">LAYER 1</span>
              <h3 class="mission__layer-title serif text-primary">Federated Learning Infrastructure</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="body-md" style="color: var(--on-surface-variant);">
              Selected teams train AI on real hospital data — without that data ever leaving the hospital. The model goes to the data. Not the other way around. Model weights, not patient records, are what moves.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mission__connector" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="mono data-sm" style="color: var(--outline);">↓</span>
          </div>

          <div class="mission__layer reveal reveal--delay-3">
            <div class="mission__layer-header">
              <span class="mono data-md text-accent mission__layer-num">LAYER 2</span>
              <h3 class="mission__layer-title serif text-primary">Certification &amp; Benchmarking</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="body-md" style="color: var(--on-surface-variant);">
              An independent evaluation process tests whether a clinical AI tool is accurate, safe, and fit for Indian clinical deployment. Pass = certification. Fail = structured feedback. Each certified model builds the benchmark. The system compounds.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .mission__inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 12rem 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4xl);
    align-items: start;
  }
  .mission__label-col {
    padding-top: 0.3rem;
    position: sticky;
    top: calc(68px + var(--space-2xl));
  }

  .mission__layers {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .mission__layer {
    padding: var(--space-xl) 0;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid rgba(196, 198, 206, 0.35);
  }
  .mission__layer:first-child { padding-top: 0; }
  .mission__layer:last-child  { border-bottom: none; }

  .mission__layer-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .mission__layer-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }
  .mission__layer-title {
    font-size: var(--headline-md);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .mission__connector {
    padding: var(--space-md) 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    padding-left: calc(var(--data-md) + var(--space-lg) + 4rem);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .mission__inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--space-2xl); }
    .mission__label-col { position: static; }
    .mission__connector { padding-left: 0; }
  }
</style>
